        "client_msg_id": "f0f5bce9-eb2f-40a0-a0ac-d3d8adf31911",
        "text": "<@UC2A2ARPT>, that's a great point. I will need to consider some of this concern area. I think I'd like to take some cues from Discord's safety UX where you cannot \"browse\" people, unless you share a community with them. Or, maybe even more precise privacy of location tooling.\nThe existence of these tools put onto the individual would probably be good, but also it could indicate more clearly that it is about \"self-organized\" groups linked by virtual communities.",
